# Version 3

### This file is installed alongside the proxy agent, and represents the list of inspectors that will be made available to all
### proxy agent plugins.  Plugins should fill in as many of these inspectors as they can.

### These inspectors are REQUIRED for the proper functioning of a proxy agent plugin.

device id: string        # A unique identifier for each device
computer name: string    # The display name of the device
data source: string      # Name of the system where data is coming from, for example "Microsoft Exchange"

### These inspectors are required for proper correlation in our correlation dashboard

correlation keys: plural correlation key
name of <correlation key>: string
value of <correlation key>: string

### These are the inspectors that a plugin must fill in in order to get accurate data displayed for each
### reserved or predefined property.  Try to fill in as many of these as possible.  If an inspector isn't
### filled in, the property will return its default value (usually blank, or "n/a").

# Device Type
device type: string

# DNS Name, Relay Name of Client
dns name: string

# OS
operating system: operating system
name of <operating system>: string
version of <operating system>: version

# IP Address, Subnet Address
network: network
ip interfaces of <network>: plural ip interface
address of <ip interface>: ipv4or6 address          # Required for IP Address
subnet address of <ip interface>: ipv4or6 address   # Required for Subnet Address
loopback of <ip interface>: boolean

#IPv6 Address
adapters of <network>: plural network adapter
up of <network adapter>: boolean
loopback of <network adapter>: boolean
ipv6 interfaces of <network adapter>: plural network adapter interface
address of <network adapter interface>: ipv4or6 address

# CPU
main processor: processor
speed of <processor>: hertz
family name of <processor>: string

# BIOS
bios: string

# Free Space on System Drive, Total Size of System Drive
system folder: folder
drive of <folder>: drive
free space of <drive>: integer
total space of <drive>: integer

# RAM
ram: ram
size of <ram>: integer

# User Name
current user: logged on user
logged on users: plural logged on user
name of <logged on user>: string



### These are generally useful inspectors that aren't part of any reserved property.

proxy agent plugin: proxy agent plugin
last report time of <proxy agent plugin>: time
version of <proxy agent plugin>: version
last device report time: time

user language: string
